Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Pop the @British pork mince{240%g} into a #mixing bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Add half of the @soy sauce{25%ml} and half the spring onion. Mix well to combine, then shape into four balls per person. Carefully thread the meatballs onto the @bamboo skewers{2} (four on each skewer), trying to spread them out evenly.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Pop the skewers onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are done when no longer pink in the middle!

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, stir in the @Jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lime{1}(zested and cut into quarters) then cut into quarters. Trim the @cucumber{½}(trimmed, halved lengthways and thinly sliced). Mix the @sugar{½%tsp}, remaining soy sauce, half the @rice vinegar{30%ml} and half the @sesame oil{24%ml} together in a large #bowl{}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a quarter of the lime juice and half the @sesame seeds{15%g}. Pop the sliced cucumber into the bowl and toss to coat. Set to one side.

Put the garlic, the remaining sesame oil and rice vinegar and two-thirds of the remaining lime juice into a small saucepan. Squeeze in the @honey{30%ml} and @Sriracha sauce{1} and stir together. Mix together the @cornflour{5%g} and the @water{3%tbsp} in a #small bowl{} until combined. Add the flour mixture to the saucepan and bring to the boil, stirring continuously. Boil for ~{30%seconds} then remove from the heat.

Once everything has finished cooking, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir in the lime zest and the remaining spring onion. Share between your plates. Pop the pork skewers on top and spoon over the sauce to coat. Sprinkle over the remaining sesame seeds and serve the cucumber salad on the side. Dig in!